James de Villiers, News24 (iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Durban - A boy was allegedly shot by a fellow pupil at a school in the Phoenix informal settlement on Friday afternoon, paramedics have said.&nbsp;Paramedics arrived at the scene and found that the 18-year-old male had sustained life-threatening injuries, said Netcare spokesperson Chris Botha in a statement."The advanced Life Support paramedic and her team worked fervently to stabilise the child," Botha said.&nbsp; The pupil was transported to a specialised hospital, where he remained in a critical condition.&nbsp;Details surrounding the incident were still unknown, but police were investigating.&nbsp; 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.